ESR measurements were carried out at 300 K. An Electron Paramagnetic Resonance (EPR) spectrometer Radiopan X-2244 was employed with a frequency (ν) of 9.3 GHz, microwave field power (P

                           mw
                        ) of ∼2 mW, the modulating field with modulation amplitude (H

                           m
                        ) of 3×10−1 mT, and modulation frequency (f) of 100 kHz. The sample thickness of 20 µm ensured negligible skin effect at temperatures exceeding 100 K.
